observations  corporate affairs  headquarters  employees  corporate culture  schism atop giant hedge fund  references  external links historyedit the firms history includes the pioneering of industry strategies such as currency overlay the separation of alpha and beta strategies the creation of absolute return products and risk parity according to financial news the company was the fastest growing asset manager from  until  when it stopped accepting new accounts its assets under management have increased by  each year during the last decade with employees at eleven times their year  levels the company’s daily observations research is reportedly read by leaders of central banks and managers of pension funds around the world  consulting research money managementedit bridgewater associates was founded by ray dalio in  from an office in his manhattan apartment at that time the business consisted exclusively of advising corporate clients and the management of domestic and international currency and interest rate risks the firm later changed its emphasis and began selling economic advice to governments and corporations such as nabisco and mcdonalds the company began publishing a paid subscription research report called the daily observations which inspired mcdonald’s corp and its main supplier to become clients in the early s another client was banks of midamerica and its treasury department director bob prince later joined bridgewater associates as cocio in  the company moved its offices from new york city to connecticut view of lake and trees surrounding the corporate headquarters in westport connecticut the companys first account was funded by a us million fixedincome investment through hilda ochoabrillembourg of world bank in  in the mids the firm changed its business focus from currency and interest rate management to global bonds and currencies for institutional investors as a fixed income and currency adviser to institutional clients the company gained a reputation as a currency trader and a developer of techniques for overlying currencies in  it launched a hedge fund portfolio using monies from kodak and loews corporation and began formally offering its currency overlay products to its clients present pure alpha all weather pure alpha major marketsedit bridgewater associates developed several innovative investment strategies during the s such as inflationindexed bonds currency overlay emerging market debt global bonds and superlong duration bonds the firm also pioneered the separation of alpha and beta investments and developed a strategy called alpha overlay which involved a portfolio of  uncorrelated investments leveraged for risk or return and combined with cash or an investment market benchmark the firm launched its pure alpha fund and began to market portable alpha investment strategies in  the pure alpha fund did well during the markets downturn of  to  and as hedge funds became more popular the company expanded its assets through its connections with various underfunded pension funds some of which were already clients in  the firm introduced its global bond overlay program in  company executives participated in the discussions at the us treasury and advised federal government on the development of inflationindexed bonds bridgewater launched its all weather hedge fund and pioneered the risk parity approach to portfolio management in  the firms assets under management grew from us billion in the mids to us billion by the year  in june  the firm was ranked as the best performing global bond manager for that year and the prior five years by pensions  investments magazine in  the company was ranked by nelson information as the worlds best money manager in recognition of the  return on its international fixed income program the firm received the global investor awards for excellenceglobal bonds award in  the following year the company received the global pensions magazine currency overlay manager of the year award and  best in class awards from the plansponsor operations survey in  the companys flagship pure alpha fund began returning money to its clients in order to maintain its investment strategy and enforce its capacity limit the firm began moving all of its clients into alternative strategies such as its pure alpha and all weather funds thereby eliminating the traditional investment approach from its portfolios that year it was honored by plansponsor magazine with the lifetime achievement award and the global pensions magazine currency manager of the year award and the money management letters public pension fund award for excellence and the alternatives manager of the year award by  the firms total assets under management grew to us billion from us billion in the year  according to a  article in barrons magazine nobody was better prepared for the global market crash than its clients and subscribers to its daily observations the company began sounding alarmsin the spring of  about the dangers of excessive financial leverage the companys researchers reviewed the public accounts of most of the major financial institutions around the globe and found that estimated future losses due to bad debts totaled us billion in december these conclusions were reported to the us treasury department when company founder ray dalio met with us treasury secretary staff and other white house economic advisers bridgewaters pure alpha fund spared its investors from most of the stock markets meltdown in  however this strategy was not successful in  when economic growth responded faster than anticipated and the dow jones industrial average increased by  while the company’s pure alpha fund reportedly gained a mere  to  senator john mccain visited the firm and addressed company employees during his  presidential campaign the teacher retirement system of texas trs invested in  million in a stake in bridgewater associates intermediate holdings lp ray dalio the companys founder began using the term dprocess in february  to describe the deleveraging and deflationary process of the subprime mortgage industry as distinct from a recession that year the company was termed the largest hedge fund in the us and it received the alternative investment news th annual hedge fund industrys lifetime achievement award and plansponsors hedge fund manager of the year award when the us gross domestic product faltered in  the firm had significant gains on their investments in treasury bonds and other securities and in november founded the us billion pure alpha major markets fund which brought the companys total assets under management to more than us billion in  the firm received several honors it was ranked number one on institutional investors worlds top  hedge funds list it received the macrofocused hedge fund firm of the year award and the aicio hedge fund industry innovation award absolute return  alpha ar ranked the company number one in its hedge fund report card and billion dollar club categories connecticut is expected to approve a plan at the end of may  which will give bridgewater associates  million in grants and loans in exchange for job training job creation and building renovations the company also must agree to retain  jobs they already support in connecticut the company could also become eligible for as much as  million in urban tax credits investment philosophyedit according to ray dalio bridgewater associates is a global macro firm it uses quantitative investment methods to identify new investments while avoiding unrealistic historical models its goal is to structure portfolios with uncorrelated investment returns based on risk allocations rather than asset allocations additionally the company is reported to only accept funds from institutional clients such as pension funds foundations endowments and central banks rather than private investors separation of alpha and betaedit the company divides its investments into two basic categories  beta investments whose returns are generated through passive management and standard market risk and  alpha investments whose goal is to generate higher returns that are uncorrelated to the general market and are actively managed the principle of separating alpha and beta investments was introduced by dalio in  and gained the recognition of other equity managers beginning in the year  the firm is reported to be the first hedge fund manager to separate alpha and beta investment strategies and offer dedicated investment funds for each systematic diversificationedit according to bloomberg bridgewater uses an investing system that combines traditional diversification with wagers on or against markets around the world and attempts to invest in instruments and markets that do not move in lock step with each other to guide its investment strategies the companys top executives have compiled hundreds of decision rules which are the financial corollary to the firms employee handbook principles and these investment guidelines have been incorporated into the firms computers analysis productsedit the firm offers three hedge funds to its clients the pure alpha fund the all weather fund and the pure alpha major markets fund it also publishes a white paper called the daily observations which is read by investors worldwide on a subscription basis pure alphaedit bridgewater associates launched its flagship fund pure alpha in  the fund is described as a diversified alpha source that invests across a group of asset classes it was designed to balance risk among a variety of noncorrelated assets through active management it includes  or  simultaneous trading positions in bonds currencies stock indexes and commodities to avoid affecting prices by concentrating funds in a single area after placing some of the companys excess cash into the pure alpha hedge fund to increase its investing discretion the fund was closed to new investors in  when it reached its predetermined maximum funds level as of  the fund is reported to have lost money in only three of its  years of existence and had an average annualized return of  the success of pure alpha is reportedly due to a portable alpha management style that trades among many asset classes all weatheredit a second fund called all weather was launched in  and highlighted low fees global inflationlinked bonds and global fixedincome investments the fund began as the founders personal trust fund and was subsequently opened to clients the goal of the fund was to create high risk adjusted returns that exceeded the return of the general market the all weather fund contains more than us billion and is one of the largest funds in the us as of  in april  after the collapse of lehman brothers the fund moved into safe portfolio mode which included nominal and inflationlinked bonds and gold instead of equities emerging market debt and commodities  pure alpha major marketsedit under the guidance of coceo jensen the firm created the pure alpha major markets in  with us billion from existing clients in the summer of  the fund was opened to a group of outside investors who had made a total advance commitment of us billion at that time it was reported to be the largest hedge fund launch the fund was established to provide an investment vehicle similar to the companys pure alpha fund but with enhanced liquidity by focusing on the major markets such as european bonds the launch of this fund in  brought the company’s total assets under management to more than us billion daily observationsedit the companys daily observations is a subscription white paper and was the flagship product and service offered by the company in  subscribers paid  per year it has been characterized as comprehensive with some editions being up to  pages in length and is reported to be one of the most widely forwarded pieces of market analysis in the industry it has been read by leaders of central banks managers of global pension funds as well as former us treasury secretary timothy geitner and president barack obama corporate affairsedit headquartersedit aerial view of the bridgewater associates corporate campus in westport connecticut in  the company moved its headquarters  miles north of new york city to wilton connecticut and in the late s it moved to a larger office space on a corporate campus in westport connecticut as the company continued to expand it became the sole tenant at the acre campus the firms headquarters is described as retreatlike and is surrounded by the trees of a former nature reserve the campus contains three buildings made of midcentury modern fieldstone and glass since  its staff has grown from  to  employees and the firm has taken office space in three additional buildings in the area in an effort to consolidate its offices the company made plans to build a  square foot headquarters in stamford ct about  miles from its present location in westport but cancelled the project in  employeesedit bridgewater associates grew from  employees in  to  employees in  the company is reported to be one of the few hedge fund managers that hires its analysts and employees right out of college and from the annual pool of graduates from ivy league schools employees are transported daily in a fancy bus that ferries them from manhattan to the companys westport offices according to an article in bloomberg about a quarter of all new hires leave within the first two years those that remain are reported to receive generous compensation and form bonds with fellow employees that are like family and the companys founder helps to pay for any employees that wish to learn the transcendental meditation technique dalio the founder relinquished his chief executive officer ceo title in july  to take on the role of mentor the companys administration consists of three coceos greg jensen eileen murray and david mccormick the former undersecretary of the treasury department the company also has three cocios chief investment officers dalio bob prince and jensen who is also coceo jensen the yearold coceo oversees the research programs at the firm and came to the company as a dartmouth college intern about  years earlier britt harris formerly of verizon investment management joined bridgewater as coceo in november  but left six months later according to dalio the cultural fit was a problem but harris is a superstar with an absolutely fabulous character from  until early  bridgewaters general counsel was james comey former united states deputy attorney general and former director of the federal bureau of investigation corporate cultureedit in  dalio saw the firm taking on hundreds of new employees and decided to create a handbook called principles which was distributed to all employees the publication is said to be part selfhelp book part management manual and part treatise on the mechanics of natural selection as they function in a business setting according to one trade journal six years after the publication of principles the firms rapid expansion led to the institution of a bizarre culture of criticism the company acknowledges that employees often encounter culture shock when they begin working there and dalio admits its not for everyone according to the companys web site employees are encouraged to be assertive and discussions about disagreements and mistakes are considered an intentional part of the companys culture because they are felt to stimulate both learning and progress a  article in new york magazine described the company as the largest and indisputably weirdest hedge fund because of its unwavering commitment to total honesty and accountability and minute detail in its corporate culture for example dalio encourages employees to do whatever it takes to make the company great and emphasizes transparency and openness in its decision making processes all meetings are recorded and can be viewed by any employee as long as the meeting topic is not proprietary in addition dalio says that he fosters an extreme meritocracy of ideas and asserts that decisions are made about investments without considerations of hierarchy he says that any employee can respectfully say anything to anyone in the firm but they must be prepared to be challenged in return the companys flat corporate structure aims to remove the barriers associated with traditional asset management firms and qualities like stodginess and riskaversion are discouraged the company has been likened to a cult but dalio denies that and insists that the firm is a dedicated community an article in the new yorker by john cassidy says that the word cult clearly has connotations that dont apply to an enterprise staffed by highly paid employees who can quit at any moment cassidy says the company is located away from other financial institutions and headed by a strongwilled leader and that employees use a unique vocabulary one client bob jacksha chief executive officer of the new mexico educational retirement board said of the firm every investment manager has its own culture and some are more unique than others schism atop giant hedge fundedit in  the wall street journal reported that dalio and greg jensen called for votes on each others conduct dalio asked the firms management and stakeholders committees if they believe jensen has integrity referencesedit coordinates °′″n °′″w﻿  ﻿°n °w﻿     a b kishan saijel september   hedge funds facing succession challenge as kovner hands off caxton to law bloomberg lp retrieved october     teitelbaum richard september   dalio returns  this year on diversified bets even as markets convulse bloomberg markets magazine retrieved october     westbrook jesse hedge funds jat bridgewater brevan howard buck august rout bloomberg lp  missing or empty url help accessdate requires url help  a b c d schultes renée september   bridgewater seeks competitive advantage through lateral thinking financial news retrieved april    dunstan barrie november   investment legends the wisdom that leads to wealth john wiley