as an institutional investment advisory service graduated to institutional investing and pioneered the risk parity investment approach in  in  the company moved its headquarters from new york city to westport connecticut and currently engages  employees it embraces a corporate culture that encourages transparency and the elimination of the decision making hierarchy and in  was the worlds largest macro hedge fund company with us billion in assets under management contents  history   consulting research money management  present pure alpha all weather pure alpha major markets  investment philosophy  separation of alpha and beta  systematic diversification  products  pure alpha  all weather  pure alpha major markets  daily observations  corporate affairs  headquarters  employees  corporate culture  schism atop giant hedge fund  references  external links historyedit the firms history includes the pioneering of industry strategies such as currency overlay the separation of alpha and beta strategies the creation of absolute return products and risk parity according to financial news the company was the fastest growing asset manager from  until  when it stopped accepting new accounts its assets under management have increased by  each year during the last decade with employees at eleven times their year  levels the company’s daily observations research is reportedly read by leaders of central banks and managers of pension funds around the world  consulting research money managementedit bridgewater associates was founded by ray dalio in  from an office in his manhattan apartment at that time the business consisted exclusively of advising corporate clients and the management of domestic and international currency and interest rate risks the firm later changed its emphasis and began selling economic advice to governments and corporations such as nabisco and mcdonalds the company began publishing a paid subscription research report called the daily observations which inspired mcdonald’s corp and its main supplier to become clients in the early s another client was banks of midamerica and its treasury department director bob prince later joined bridgewater associates as cocio in  the company moved its offices from new york city to connecticut view of lake and trees surrounding the corporate headquarters in westport connecticut the companys first account was funded by a us million fixedincome investment through hilda ochoabrillembourg of world bank in  in the mids the firm changed its business focus from currency and interest rate management to global bonds and currencies for institutional investors as a fixed income and currency adviser to institutional clients the company gained a reputation as a currency trader and a developer of techniques for overlying currencies in  it launched a hedge fund portfolio using monies from kodak and loews corporation and began formally offering its currency overlay products to its clients present pure alpha all weather pure alpha major marketsedit bridgewater associates developed several innovative investment strategies during the s such as inflationindexed bonds currency overlay emerging market debt global bonds and superlong duration bonds the firm also pioneered the separation of alpha and beta investments and developed a strategy called alpha overlay which involved a portfolio of  uncorrelated investments leveraged for risk or return and combined with cash or an investment market benchmark the firm launched its pure alpha fund and began to market portable alpha investment strategies in  the pure alpha fund did well during the markets downturn of  to  and as hedge funds became more popular the company expanded its assets through its connections with various underfunded pension funds some of which were already clients in  the firm introduced its global bond overlay program in  company executives participated in the discussions at the us treasury and advised federal government on the development of infl